HEADWORD: Cloven
<hw>Clo"ven</hw> <pr>(kl⟦omac⟧"v'n)</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos>
<def>from <er>Cleave</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To show the cloven foot</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>To show the cloven hoof</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to reveal a
devilish character, or betray an evil purpose, notwithstanding
disguises, -- Satan being represented dramatically and symbolically as
having cloven hoofs.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cloven-hoofed</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Cloven-footed</ent>⟦br⟧
